sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1033282
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: amilCP blue chromoprotein with strong promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Blue/purple chromoprotein (amilCP: [[BBa_K592009]]) with strong promotor (CP29). The promoter is supposed to work in E. coli as well as Lactobacillus.
(Construct name: pSB1C3-CP29-B0034-amilCP)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anders Edlund, Mikael Strandgren

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1033930
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This chromoprotein from the coral Acropora millepora, amilCP, naturally exhibits strong color when expressed. The protein has an absorbance maximum at 588 nm giving it a blue/purple color visible to the naked eye, thereby requiring no instruments to observe. The strong color is readily observed in both LB or agar culture, in less than 24 hours of incubation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Lundin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Illegal internal restriction site had to be removed (EcoRI).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1033222
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for a promoter that works in both E. coli and L. bacillus. It is characterized agains J23101, when J23101 had 4322 AU, this promoter had 15861 AU.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephanie Herman, Alona Nyberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is a synthetic promoter based on a promoter library from the article "The Sequence of Spacers between the Consensus Sequences Modulates the Strength of Prokaryotic Promoters." by Peter Ruhdal Jensen and Karin Hammer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is designed with the same sticky ends as you would get by cutting it with EcoRI-HF and Spel.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: amilCP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This chromoprotein, amilCP, naturally exhibits very strong color when expressed. The color is blue/purple and is visible to naked eye, thereby requiring no instruments to observe. This DNA was provided by Jeffrey Miller at UCLA. It was made BioBrick-compatible after removal of one illegal internal restriction site (EcoRI).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Illegal internal restriction site had to be removed (EcoRI).
